The paper deals with algorithms for Boolean matrix decomposition, which is a problem in data mining and machine learning. The paper proposes two heuristic algorithms for finding suboptimal but good decomposition, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-categories of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), data mining (cs.DM), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of exact mathematical formulas and the condition of interpretability, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-categories of information theory (cs.IT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
